functions.name: DCheckImpl
functions.logic: Implements the DCHECK macro.  It's called when a DCHECK condition fails.  It likely performs some kind of logging or error reporting (possibly assertion failure) based on the provided message and source location.  This is a debug-only check.

functions.name: FatalImpl
functions.logic: Implements the CHECK macro. Called when a CHECK condition fails. This function is expected to terminate the program after logging an error with the provided message and source location. The `[[noreturn]]` attribute indicates that this function does not return.
